        "timestamp": "2020-02-29 22:08:03.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n> \n> (1 comment)\n> \n> > This is the consolidated version of the review which I abandoned\n>  > https://gerrit.onap.org/r/#/c/policy/xacml-pdp/+/101557/\n>  > \n>  > All the previous comments have been addressed and integrated in\n>  > this review. It can build now.\n> \n> Congratulations on getting it to build successfully!\n> \n> Question: Should responses be encoded using the same media type as the request?  Or should they simply be test/plain or simple application/json?\n\nI'm going to force that if they send XML, we return XML. The Content-Type and Accepts have to match. No mixing, although it should be possible. We can tackle that in another release. But I can't see someone want to send XML and get JSON back. If they are using one or the other most likely they would not mix.",
        "patchset_number": 1
